---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
import FoilTemplate from '../../components/FoilTemplate.astro';

const body = `[YOUR DATE]

[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR ADDRESS]
[YOUR EMAIL]

Records Access Officer
[DISTRICT NAME]
[DISTRICT ADDRESS]

Re: Freedom of Information Law request — vendor Data Protection Agreements and Parents Bill of Rights for Data Privacy

Dear Records Access Officer:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law (Public Officers Law Article 6) and in connection with the rights established by Education Law §2-d and 8 NYCRR Part 121, I request copies of the following records:

1. The district's Parents Bill of Rights for Data Privacy, in the form currently posted or maintained, and any prior versions in effect during the past three school years.

2. Every signed Data Protection Agreement (DPA) between the district and a third-party contractor or service provider that has access to student personally identifiable information (PII), as defined in Education Law §2-d(1)(c) and Part 121.1(j). This includes, without limitation, agreements with:
   - Google (Workspace for Education and any related services),
   - The device manufacturer and any device-management vendor,
   - Any classroom-monitoring or content-filtering vendor (e.g., GoGuardian, Gaggle, Securly, Lightspeed),
   - Any learning management system vendor,
   - Any assessment, adaptive-learning, or analytics vendor,
   - Any single-sign-on or roster-management vendor (e.g., Clever, ClassLink),
   - Any communication or behavior-management vendor (e.g., ClassDojo, Remind, Seesaw).

3. The supplemental information document required by Part 121.3 for each DPA listed in (2).

4. The current public list (or website page) on which the district maintains its inventory of contractors and service providers with access to student PII.

I request electronic delivery (PDF or original electronic format) where possible, to my email address above. Please advise in advance if any portion of this request will incur fees over $5.

If any portion of this request is denied, please cite the specific statutory exemption relied on, and please provide the records that are not subject to that exemption.

Please acknowledge this request within five business days as required by §89(3) of the Public Officers Law.

Thank you for your assistance.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]`;
---

<Layout title="FOIL — vendor DPAs and Parents Bill of Rights">
  <article class="prose-measure mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mb-1"><a href="/foil/">← All FOIL templates</a></p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">FOIL: vendor DPAs and Parents Bill of Rights</h1>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-1">What this gets you</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700">Every signed Data Protection Agreement the district has with a vendor that handles your child's data, plus the district's Parents Bill of Rights for Data Privacy. Required by §2-d and Part 121.</p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-1">Where to send it</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700">The district's Records Access Officer.</p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-1">What to expect</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-stone-700">
      <li>5 business days to acknowledge.</li>
      <li>20 business days to respond, deny, or specify a reasonable later date.</li>
      <li>If the district claims trade-secret exemption on a DPA, the §2-d clauses (privacy and security terms) are still public; only narrow commercial terms can be redacted.</li>
    </ul>

    <FoilTemplate
      title="Template letter"
      description="Replace bracketed fields. The vendor list is intentionally broad — the district may not have agreements with all of these, and that's useful information too."
      body={body}
    />

    <div class="disclaimer mt-8">
      Template, not legal advice.
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
